that you were watching?

759
00:43:54,980 --> 00:43:57,243
Yes, she was aware.

760
00:43:57,286 --> 00:43:59,985
- She-- she knew you were...
- She knew I was absolutely
watching.

761
00:44:00,028 --> 00:44:02,683
[ both laughing ]

762
00:44:02,727 --> 00:44:05,555
Jane's voice: 
Perfect for you, 
Michael, isn't it?

763
00:44:05,599 --> 00:44:07,296
 Get rid of Jane.

764
00:44:08,515 --> 00:44:11,257
Jane:
Hello? Um, who is this?

765
00:44:11,300 --> 00:44:13,607
Woman: 
Who is this? 
You called me.

766
00:44:13,651 --> 00:44:15,740
Uh, this is Jane.

767
00:44:15,783 --> 00:44:19,004
Um, is Tom there?

768
00:44:19,047 --> 00:44:21,789
Jane, it's Ellie.

769
00:44:21,833 --> 00:44:23,704
You sound so peculiar.

770
00:44:23,748 --> 00:44:27,273
Well, I--
I just got over the flu.

771
00:44:27,316 --> 00:44:29,536
Um, I need to talk
to Tom.

772
00:44:29,579 --> 00:44:32,017
 You know Tom doesn't get home 
till after 10:00.

773
00:44:32,060 --> 00:44:33,888
Right.
Oh, right, right.

774
00:44:33,932 --> 00:44:35,542
Um, Ellie,

775
00:44:35,585 --> 00:44:38,937
did Michael call

776
00:44:38,980 --> 00:44:41,461
and ask if I was there?

777
00:44:41,504 --> 00:44:44,899
Why would he ask
if you were here?

778
00:44:44,943 --> 00:44:47,206
Ellie, please,
you gotta listen.

779
00:44:47,249 --> 00:44:49,251
Something--
something's happened to me

780
00:44:49,295 --> 00:44:52,777
[ stammering ]
and I can't remember
who I am

781
00:44:52,820 --> 00:44:55,388
and it's very hard
for me to focus.

782
00:44:55,431 --> 00:44:57,172
 [ dog barks ]

783
00:44:57,216 --> 00:44:59,871
Jane, is Michael there?

784
00:44:59,914 --> 00:45:02,482
- Can I speak to him?
- No, no, you just
have to listen.

785
00:45:02,525 --> 00:45:05,267
You have to listen.
Now-- now, Michael
told the police

786
00:45:05,311 --> 00:45:08,096
that, um-- that, um,

787
00:45:08,140 --> 00:45:11,621
I went to visit
my brother in San Diego.

788
00:45:11,665 --> 00:45:13,275
But then I found
my purse.

789
00:45:13,319 --> 00:45:16,583
 How could I have gone 
to San Diego

790
00:45:16,626 --> 00:45:19,238
 if I didn't have my purse 
with all my ID?

791
00:45:19,281 --> 00:45:21,762
You've gotta tell Tom
to come and get me.

792
00:45:21,806 --> 00:45:24,112
You've gotta tell him
to come and get me right now.

793
00:45:24,156 --> 00:45:25,723
 [ line clicks ]

794
00:45:25,766 --> 00:45:28,334
 Ellie, it's Michael.

795
00:45:28,377 --> 00:45:30,684
Michael,
what's going on?

796
00:45:30,728 --> 00:45:32,338
I'm sorry
to get you involved.

797
00:45:32,381 --> 00:45:34,122
I didn't wanna worry
you and Tom.

798
00:45:35,645 --> 00:45:37,386
Jane's having
some kind of breakdown.

799
00:45:37,430 --> 00:45:39,258
I think it's related
to the accident.

800
00:45:39,301 --> 00:45:41,216
 She's under doctor's care

801
00:45:41,260 --> 00:45:42,478
 and we're doing 
the best we can.

802
00:45:42,522 --> 00:45:44,132
 Don't wanna worry you

803
00:45:44,176 --> 00:45:45,917
 and they say 
she's gonna be fine,

804
00:45:45,960 --> 00:45:48,049
 so, okay, don't worry.

805
00:45:48,093 --> 00:45:49,964
 Give my best to Tom, 
please.

806
00:45:50,008 --> 00:45:52,358
 I'll talk to you later.

807
00:46:09,941 --> 00:46:12,726
Excuse me.
Can I help you?

808
00:46:12,770 --> 00:46:15,903
Um, yes.
Can you tell me
what these are?

809
00:46:18,079 --> 00:46:19,689
Where'd you get these?

810
00:46:20,952 --> 00:46:22,823
They're Ativan, right?

811
00:46:22,867 --> 00:46:24,651
Who told you
they were Ativan?

812
00:46:26,131 --> 00:46:28,220
Well,
what are they, then?

813
00:46:28,263 --> 00:46:30,091
It's Haldol.

814
00:46:30,135 --> 00:46:32,006
Something you don't
wanna mess with.

815
00:46:32,050 --> 00:46:34,356
 Listen, you haven't 
been taking these, 
have you,

816
00:46:34,400 --> 00:46:35,836
 without a prescription?

817
00:46:35,880 --> 00:46:37,664
Well, I had trouble
sleeping

818
00:46:37,707 --> 00:46:40,362
and a friend
gave them to me.

819
00:46:42,190 --> 00:46:44,018
First,
get rid of the pills,

820
00:46:44,062 --> 00:46:45,541
then you get rid
of the friend.

821
00:46:45,585 --> 00:46:47,152
 Otherwise, 
it can cause you

822
00:46:47,195 --> 00:46:49,197
 severe, 
irreversible symptoms--

823
00:46:49,241 --> 00:46:52,244
 uncontrollable movements 
like Parkinson's disease.

824
00:46:52,287 --> 00:46:55,813
Haldol is a drug
of last resort
for psychosis.

825
00:47:06,127 --> 00:47:07,781
Jane?

826
00:47:12,786 --> 00:47:14,875
- What is it?
- Don't you touch me.

827
00:47:14,919 --> 00:47:17,617
 Just stay away.

828
00:47:17,660 --> 00:47:20,011
What are you trying
to do to me?

829
00:47:21,360 --> 00:47:23,579
Dr. Melloff
prescribed Ativan.

830
00:47:23,623 --> 00:47:25,843
You've been giving me
Haldol.

831
00:47:25,886 --> 00:47:27,409
Haldol?

832
00:47:27,453 --> 00:47:29,063
You tell me
this is Ativan?

833
00:47:35,069 --> 00:47:37,593
Jane, where did you
get this?

834
00:47:37,637 --> 00:47:39,378
Huh? Did you get these
from my bag?

835
00:47:39,421 --> 00:47:41,641
Oh, now you're saying
that you didn't
give that to me?

836
00:47:41,684 --> 00:47:43,512
Of course I didn't
give these to you.
What, you think I'm crazy?

837
00:47:43,556 --> 00:47:46,124
- No, I think you're lying!
- Jane, why would I lie to you?

838
00:47:46,167 --> 00:47:49,388
What happened between us,
Michael, that you don't
want me to remember?

839
00:47:49,431 --> 00:47:50,998
What happened?

840
00:47:53,435 --> 00:47:55,394
Jane, I don't think
you should push this

841
00:47:55,437 --> 00:47:57,091
- until you're 
feeling better.
- No, no, no.

842
00:47:57,135 --> 00:47:58,701
I'm not gonna wait
until my brain is fried

843
00:47:58,745 --> 00:48:00,442
and I can't think
anymore!

844
00:48:03,968 --> 00:48:06,144
Michael, when I was
wandering the streets
that day,

845
00:48:06,187 --> 00:48:09,060
I-- I found

846
00:48:09,103 --> 00:48:11,627
hundred-dollar bills
in my pockets

847
00:48:11,671 --> 00:48:14,065
and my dress was covered
with blood.

848
00:48:16,937 --> 00:48:18,678
Does that ring a bell?

849
00:48:20,158 --> 00:48:22,377
What about the blood,
Michael?

850
00:48:22,421 --> 00:48:24,989
Where did the blood
come from?

851
00:48:27,426 --> 00:48:29,471
All right, look.
A year ago...

852
00:48:31,212 --> 00:48:33,301
[ sighs ]
...when your mother
was killed,

853
00:48:33,345 --> 00:48:36,217
you went into
a severe depression

854
00:48:36,261 --> 00:48:39,525
 and the doctors called it 
survivor's guilt.

855
00:48:39,568 --> 00:48:42,354
They prescribed Haldol.

856
00:48:42,397 --> 00:48:45,009
 It worked.

857
00:48:45,052 --> 00:48:46,706
For a while,
everything seemed okay.

858
00:48:46,749 --> 00:48:48,534
You--
yeah, you even

859
00:48:48,577 --> 00:48:52,277
started running
with Daniel next door
a few days a week.

860
00:48:53,713 --> 00:48:56,237
 And then it was 
every day.

861
00:48:56,281 --> 00:48:58,196
 And then,

862
00:48:58,239 --> 00:49:01,242
well, running
wasn't enough.

863
00:49:02,852 --> 00:49:05,159
So I had an affair?

864
00:49:07,988 --> 00:49:09,729
What about the money?

865
00:49:09,772 --> 00:49:11,470
[ sighs ]
It was from
our joint account.

866
00:49:13,472 --> 00:49:16,301
The bank called me and said
that you'd withdrawn $10,000,

867
00:49:16,344 --> 00:49:18,085
 closed the account.

868
00:49:18,129 --> 00:49:20,087
 I assumed that 
you were running off

869
00:49:20,131 --> 00:49:22,611
with one of your lovers.

870
00:49:22,655 --> 00:49:23,917
I came running home.

871
00:49:23,961 --> 00:49:25,484
You were hysterical.

872
00:49:25,527 --> 00:49:26,876
You were packing.

873
00:49:26,920 --> 00:49:28,922
Said you were
leaving me.

874
00:49:28,966 --> 00:49:31,316
Said that I didn't deserve
to live with someone
like you.

875
00:49:31,359 --> 00:49:32,970
I argued, I said no.

876
00:49:33,013 --> 00:49:34,797
We fought, you hit me.

877
00:49:34,841 --> 00:49:38,062
And there was blood
everywhere.

878
00:49:42,066 --> 00:49:44,198
You said
survivor's guilt.

879
00:49:46,461 --> 00:49:49,160
Was I in the car
with my mother?

880
00:49:52,293 --> 00:49:54,382
You were driving.

881
00:49:57,603 --> 00:50:00,388
You were in a hurry.

882
00:50:00,432 --> 00:50:03,522
You, uh,
missed a turn.

883
00:50:03,565 --> 00:50:07,091
Witnesses said
that you didn't signal

884
00:50:07,134 --> 00:50:09,702
and some car

885
00:50:09,745 --> 00:50:12,139
slammed into
the passenger side.

886
00:50:18,754 --> 00:50:20,713
- What else?
- No.

887
00:50:20,756 --> 00:50:22,541
No, no, you have to
tell me the truth.

888
00:50:22,584 --> 00:50:24,673
- You have to tell me
everything.
- Nothing.

889
00:50:24,717 --> 00:50:25,979
Please.

890
00:50:26,023 --> 00:50:28,373
Amy.

891
00:50:31,115 --> 00:50:33,334
[ sighs ]

892
00:50:33,378 --> 00:50:36,294
Amy was in the backseat
behind your mother.

893
00:50:38,035 --> 00:50:42,082
 She died in your arms

894
00:50:42,126 --> 00:50:44,171
waiting for
the ambulance.

895
00:50:45,651 --> 00:50:47,870
[ whimpers ]

896
00:50:47,914 --> 00:50:49,655
[ crying ]
Oh, no, I didn't--

897
00:50:49,698 --> 00:50:51,265
I didn't do that.
I didn't do that.

898
00:50:51,309 --> 00:50:53,311
- [ stammering ]
- I'm sorry.

899
00:50:55,443 --> 00:50:57,402
[ sobs ]

900
00:51:05,149 --> 00:51:06,889
Sarah:
Hi, sweetie.

901
00:51:08,152 --> 00:51:09,762
 Hi.

902
00:51:09,805 --> 00:51:11,981
 Hi, it's Sarah.

903
00:51:12,025 --> 00:51:13,809
And--
and Peter's here.

904
00:51:13,853 --> 00:51:16,203
We came to see you.

905
00:51:18,379 --> 00:51:22,079
Honey, oh-- oh, my God.
[ cries ]

906
00:51:22,122 --> 00:51:24,124
It's okay.

907
00:51:26,170 --> 00:51:28,041
She's not in any pain.

908
00:51:28,085 --> 00:51:30,435
Can she hear me or...?

909
00:51:30,478 --> 00:51:32,263
Jane?

910
00:51:32,306 --> 00:51:34,047
It's Sarah and Peter.

911
00:51:34,091 --> 00:51:38,269
- Can you say hello?
- Jane's voice: Sarah? Jane?

912
00:51:38,312 --> 00:51:41,054
 Peter? Hello.

913
00:51:41,098 --> 00:51:44,144
I-- Michael,

914
00:51:44,188 --> 00:51:46,799
I don't understand this.
I don't understand this.

915
00:51:46,842 --> 00:51:49,149
I mean, I know
she suffered
a major trauma,

916
00:51:49,193 --> 00:51:50,933
but this is Jane,
for God's sake.

917
00:51:50,977 --> 00:51:52,631
- Shh.
- She's always
been in control.

918
00:51:52,674 --> 00:51:55,068
She's always been--
Janey?

919
00:51:55,112 --> 00:51:58,376
Jane, you've gotta
break out of this.

920
00:51:58,419 --> 00:51:59,594
Please.

921
00:51:59,638 --> 00:52:01,901
She's not
getting better.

922
00:52:01,944 --> 00:52:03,859
She can barely
open her eyes.

923
00:52:03,903 --> 00:52:08,168
Michael, maybe you shouldn't
be caring for her at home.

924
00:52:08,212 --> 00:52:09,735
Why not?

925
00:52:09,778 --> 00:52:12,085
I just think she might
get better care

926
00:52:12,129 --> 00:52:13,739
at a hospital or,
you know, a facility.

927
00:52:13,782 --> 00:52:15,349
Peter, I'm not
putting Jane anywhere.

928
00:52:15,393 --> 00:52:16,524
She belongs
here at home

929
00:52:16,568 --> 00:52:18,004
where she's,
you know--

930
00:52:18,047 --> 00:52:19,440
she's surrounded
by love.

931
00:52:19,484 --> 00:52:21,007
She's been home,
Michael,

932
00:52:21,050 --> 00:52:23,096
and she's
going downhill.

933
00:52:26,186 --> 00:52:27,579
Tracy, you remember,

934
00:52:27,622 --> 00:52:29,972
my friend who thought
she was pregnant?

935
00:52:30,016 --> 00:52:32,845
Turns out it was
early menopause.

936
00:52:32,888 --> 00:52:34,325
Is that disgusting?

937
00:52:34,368 --> 00:52:35,935
Men can start
a family at 80,

938
00:52:35,978 --> 00:52:38,764
but women are
washed up at 40.

939
00:52:38,807 --> 00:52:40,983
You heard me,
didn't you?

940
00:52:42,637 --> 00:52:45,074
I knew you were
in there.

941
00:52:45,118 --> 00:52:47,207
Please, Janey,
come out.

942
00:52:47,251 --> 00:52:49,383
 It's so great 
out here

943
00:52:49,427 --> 00:52:51,820
even with early
menopause.

944
00:52:53,257 --> 00:52:54,606
But-- but, listen,

945
00:52:54,649 --> 00:52:55,955
Peter's trying
to talk Michael

946
00:52:55,998 --> 00:52:57,696
into institutionalizing you.

947
00:52:57,739 --> 00:53:00,612
- So, please,
- Jane's voice: Go away.

948
00:53:00,655 --> 00:53:03,223
- you've got to fight.
- Jane's voice: Just go away.

