where it's private?

1260
01:10:32,619 --> 01:10:34,360
Not Andrew.

1261
01:10:36,319 --> 01:10:38,190
Who, honey?

1262
01:10:38,234 --> 01:10:41,237
Tell Mommy
who touched you.

1263
01:10:48,548 --> 01:10:50,550
[ whispers ]
Daddy.

1264
01:10:54,075 --> 01:10:56,034
Jane. Jane,
what's going on?

1265
01:10:56,077 --> 01:10:58,906
You miserable bastard.

1266
01:10:58,950 --> 01:11:00,343
What's the matter?

1267
01:11:00,386 --> 01:11:02,345
I went to see
Amy's teacher today.

1268
01:11:02,388 --> 01:11:03,911
So?

1269
01:11:03,955 --> 01:11:07,306
So she thinks Amy's
been sexually abused.

1270
01:11:07,350 --> 01:11:09,526
What?
That's impossible.

1271
01:11:09,569 --> 01:11:10,831
Well, that's
what I thought.

1272
01:11:10,875 --> 01:11:12,572
And then
I talked to Amy.

1273
01:11:12,616 --> 01:11:14,705
How could you?

1274
01:11:14,748 --> 01:11:16,097
You're her father.

1275
01:11:16,141 --> 01:11:18,274
You lousy
son of a bitch!

1276
01:11:18,317 --> 01:11:20,276
Me? Jane, you're upset.

1277
01:11:20,319 --> 01:11:22,190
Don't play games
with me, Michael!

1278
01:11:22,234 --> 01:11:24,584
Excuse me,
but will you listen
to what you're saying?

1279
01:11:24,628 --> 01:11:26,934
You really believe
I'm capable of, what,

1280
01:11:26,978 --> 01:11:29,067
- molesting my own daughter?
- I believe her.

1281
01:11:29,110 --> 01:11:31,025
Well, how can you
be so sure?

1282
01:11:31,069 --> 01:11:33,114
She's a child,
she's got an imagination,

1283
01:11:33,158 --> 01:11:34,855
- she watches television.
- She's telling the truth.

1284
01:11:34,899 --> 01:11:36,944
[ scoffs ]
What? So, what,
kids never lie?

1285
01:11:36,988 --> 01:11:38,250
Kids never make things up?

1286
01:11:38,294 --> 01:11:39,686
I believe her, Michael.

1287
01:11:39,730 --> 01:11:41,340
Well, so how can you
be so sure?!

1288
01:11:41,384 --> 01:11:42,689
Because she loves you!

1289
01:11:42,733 --> 01:11:44,691
Because it broke
her heart to tell me

1290
01:11:44,735 --> 01:11:47,607
and because I know
when my daughter's
telling the truth.

1291
01:11:47,651 --> 01:11:49,566
Well, sure,
'cause you know everything.

1292
01:11:49,609 --> 01:11:51,307
Right?
Jane knows it all!

1293
01:11:51,350 --> 01:11:53,874
Slug a guy
in the library,

1294
01:11:53,918 --> 01:11:55,267
- it's the guy's fault.
- Oh, come on, Michael,
that has nothing to do--

1295
01:11:55,311 --> 01:11:56,312
 Jane, who the hell 
are you?

1296
01:11:56,355 --> 01:11:57,965
Huh?

1297
01:11:58,009 --> 01:11:59,663
I've been married to you
for 12 years.

1298
01:11:59,706 --> 01:12:00,794
 I don't know anymore!

1299
01:12:00,838 --> 01:12:02,143
You know something?

1300
01:12:02,187 --> 01:12:03,971
If somebody
molested my daughter,

1301
01:12:04,015 --> 01:12:06,800
- I'm gonna kill him!
- Oh, Michael.

1302
01:12:06,844 --> 01:12:09,716
It's always somebody else,
isn't it?

1303
01:12:09,760 --> 01:12:12,371
Amy's lying,
Jane's crazy.

1304
01:12:12,415 --> 01:12:15,026
Well, this is it.
It's over.

1305
01:12:15,069 --> 01:12:17,942
- [ clinking ]
- You're never gonna
touch your daughter again.

1306
01:12:17,985 --> 01:12:21,815
What the hell are you--
what the hell are you
gonna do, huh?

1307
01:12:21,859 --> 01:12:23,208
The hell you think
you're doing?

1308
01:12:23,251 --> 01:12:25,210
What, you got
medical proof, huh?

1309
01:12:25,253 --> 01:12:26,472
 You're gonna drag 
our daughter through court?

1310
01:12:26,516 --> 01:12:28,126
You're gonna fight
for custody?

1311
01:12:28,169 --> 01:12:29,910
Oh, you're damn right
I'm gonna fight for custody!

1312
01:12:29,954 --> 01:12:32,043
Well, you're
not gonna get it
'cause you're unfit!

1313
01:12:32,086 --> 01:12:34,524
- And I can prove it!
- [ screams ]

1314
01:12:36,003 --> 01:12:38,310
[ grunts ]

1315
01:12:38,354 --> 01:12:39,703
[ gasps ]

1316
01:12:50,017 --> 01:12:51,715
[ Jane gasps ]

1317
01:12:54,587 --> 01:12:57,416
Jane: 
And then I found myself 
wandering.

1318
01:12:57,460 --> 01:13:00,680
 That was it. 
I'd forgotten everything.

1319
01:13:00,724 --> 01:13:04,554
Oh, please not Michael.

1320
01:13:04,597 --> 01:13:06,686
Jane, I really think
we need to get home.

1321
01:13:06,730 --> 01:13:09,472
Of course you don't
believe any of this,
do you?

1322
01:13:12,344 --> 01:13:14,215
Give me your keys.

1323
01:13:26,924 --> 01:13:29,405
 [ birds chirping ]

1324
01:13:34,105 --> 01:13:36,455
[ siren blaring ]

1325
01:13:36,499 --> 01:13:38,762
Oh, no, not now.

1326
01:13:42,983 --> 01:13:44,594
I can't pull over.

1327
01:13:44,637 --> 01:13:47,727
Oh, no.
[ gasps ]

1328
01:13:51,035 --> 01:13:52,602
[ sighs ]

1329
01:14:15,451 --> 01:14:17,540
[ touch tones beeping ]

1330
01:14:24,938 --> 01:14:27,463
 [ phone ringing ]

1331
01:14:40,954 --> 01:14:43,957
 [ line rings ]

1332
01:14:45,524 --> 01:14:48,614
 [ ringing continues ]

1333
01:14:53,663 --> 01:14:56,274
- [ line ringing ]
- [ sighs ]

1334
01:15:23,736 --> 01:15:25,172
 [ car door closes ]

1335
01:15:37,054 --> 01:15:39,317
There we go, lady.

1336
01:15:39,360 --> 01:15:41,319
We'll put the groceries
in the kitchen.

1337
01:15:41,362 --> 01:15:43,190
You run along
and wash up for lunch, honey.

1338
01:15:44,757 --> 01:15:47,368
I found out
that the pony rides
start at 3:00.

1339
01:15:47,412 --> 01:15:49,283
So she can have
a nice lunch

1340
01:15:49,327 --> 01:15:50,894
 and then we'll 
surprise her.

1341
01:15:50,937 --> 01:15:53,810
Oh, she's gonna like that.

1342
01:15:53,853 --> 01:15:55,986
Do you think so?

1343
01:15:56,029 --> 01:15:58,249
Honey, don't worry so.

1344
01:15:58,292 --> 01:16:00,338
She's gonna be
all right.

1345
01:16:06,910 --> 01:16:09,434
[ whispers ]
Where were you, Mommy?

1346
01:16:09,477 --> 01:16:13,481
You said to wait for you
and I waited and waited
and you never came.

1347
01:16:13,525 --> 01:16:17,311
I know, sweetheart,
but Mommy got very sick
and couldn't come back.

1348
01:16:17,355 --> 01:16:19,618
But that's all over now
and we're gonna
go away together

1349
01:16:19,662 --> 01:16:22,099
just like we planned,
just the two of us.

1350
01:16:25,885 --> 01:16:27,713
Grandmother: 
Amy, honey?

1351
01:16:28,975 --> 01:16:31,587
Amy, I--

1352
01:16:31,630 --> 01:16:33,806
I'm taking Amy
back to town.

1353
01:16:33,850 --> 01:16:35,678
You're not going
anywhere with her.

1354
01:16:35,721 --> 01:16:37,854
Honey, you're
frightening the baby.

1355
01:16:37,897 --> 01:16:40,465
Jane, let's talk
about this sensibly.

1356
01:16:40,508 --> 01:16:41,945
There's nothing to say.
Come on, honey.

1357
01:16:44,469 --> 01:16:46,993
Amy, come to Grandma,
darling.

1358
01:16:47,037 --> 01:16:48,865
Don't get involved,
Doris.

1359
01:16:48,908 --> 01:16:50,736
This is between
your son and me.

1360
01:16:52,695 --> 01:16:55,523
Amy, I want you to go outside
and stand on the front porch

1361
01:16:55,567 --> 01:16:57,613
and wait for me.
I have to talk to
Grandma and Grandpa.

1362
01:16:57,656 --> 01:16:59,136
I'll be right out, okay?

1363
01:16:59,179 --> 01:17:01,486
Grandmother: 
Amy.

1364
01:17:01,529 --> 01:17:03,662
Don't you wanna give
Grandma and Grandpa
a goodbye kiss?

1365
01:17:03,706 --> 01:17:05,795
I don't think
that would be

1366
01:17:05,838 --> 01:17:07,231
such a good idea, Amy.

1367
01:17:07,274 --> 01:17:09,886
Why don't you
just throw them a kiss?

1368
01:17:21,985 --> 01:17:24,161
Grandmother: 
So Michael's not enough, huh?

1369
01:17:24,204 --> 01:17:26,206
You're gonna tell her
a lot of lies about us, too.

1370
01:17:26,250 --> 01:17:28,818
I don't have a problem
with you and Bert, Doris.

1371
01:17:28,861 --> 01:17:30,776
You love Amy.
I know that.

1372
01:17:30,820 --> 01:17:32,735
The problem
is with Michael.

1373
01:17:32,778 --> 01:17:35,520
- He's been telling you lies.
- Michael doesn't lie, Jane.

1374
01:17:35,563 --> 01:17:38,697
We're not gonna let you
hurt Michael like this, Jane.

1375
01:17:38,741 --> 01:17:41,308
Do you realize
what you're doing?

1376
01:17:41,352 --> 01:17:43,006
 You're gonna lose 
everything.

1377
01:17:43,049 --> 01:17:46,357
Michael's going to keep Amy
and his practice.

1378
01:17:46,400 --> 01:17:48,185
Never.

1379
01:17:49,621 --> 01:17:50,883
Jane: 
"Rikki-Tikki had a right

1380
01:17:50,927 --> 01:17:52,450
 to be proud of himself.

1381
01:17:52,493 --> 01:17:54,408
But he did not grow
too proud

1382
01:17:54,452 --> 01:17:57,629
and he kept that garden
as a mongoose should keep it

1383
01:17:57,673 --> 01:18:00,066
with tooth and jump
and spring and bite

1384
01:18:00,110 --> 01:18:04,070
till never a cobra
dared show its head
inside the walls."

1385
01:18:06,377 --> 01:18:08,640
 [ horn honks 
in distance ]

1386
01:18:21,218 --> 01:18:23,655
Sarah: 
Now will you tell me 
what's been going on?

1387
01:18:23,699 --> 01:18:25,875
Well, when we left
the cottage,

1388
01:18:25,918 --> 01:18:28,616
 I was afraid of Michael, 
so we drove straight to 
the D.A.'s office.

1389
01:18:28,660 --> 01:18:32,055
He listened politely,
but then said he needed
more evidence.

1390
01:18:32,098 --> 01:18:35,711
A seven-year-old child,
it's her word against his.

1391
01:18:35,754 --> 01:18:37,669
So I hired a lawyer

1392
01:18:37,713 --> 01:18:39,758
 and she's 
been tracking down 
Michael's patients.

1393
01:18:39,802 --> 01:18:43,109
And we hit pay dirt
with a Mrs. Klinger.

1394
01:18:43,153 --> 01:18:45,546
- She's on her way over.
- [ exhales ]

1395
01:18:45,590 --> 01:18:47,940
[ knocks ]

1396
01:18:47,984 --> 01:18:49,681
Oh, I'm so glad
you're here.

1397
01:18:49,725 --> 01:18:52,118
- Please come in.
- I can't stay long.

1398
01:18:52,162 --> 01:18:54,642
Mu husband is waiting
in the car.

1399
01:18:54,686 --> 01:18:57,776
- He's not coming up?
- I can only stay a minute.

1400
01:18:57,820 --> 01:18:59,473
Oh, please don't say
what I think you're
gonna say.

1401
01:18:59,517 --> 01:19:01,345
I'm sorry,
Mrs. Ravenson.

1402
01:19:01,388 --> 01:19:04,217
I know you were counting on us
and I hate to disappoint you--

1403
01:19:04,261 --> 01:19:07,003
Then don't, please.

1404
01:19:07,046 --> 01:19:09,875
Mrs. Klinger: 
My husband and I argued 
all last night about it.

1405
01:19:09,919 --> 01:19:12,965
He's adamant.
He won't let Lisa testify.

1406
01:19:16,099 --> 01:19:19,363
My husband
molested your child.

1407
01:19:19,406 --> 01:19:21,800
We have no proof.

1408
01:19:21,844 --> 01:19:23,497
Do you believe her?

1409
01:19:25,630 --> 01:19:27,458
Yes, I do.

1410
01:19:27,501 --> 01:19:29,677
But who else is gonna believe
a five-year-old?

1411
01:19:29,721 --> 01:19:32,158
My daughter is also
going to testify

1412
01:19:32,202 --> 01:19:34,465
and my attorney is going through
Dr. Ravenson's files

1413
01:19:34,508 --> 01:19:38,251
- to see if there's
any other children--
- Lisa has been through so much.

1414
01:19:38,295 --> 01:19:43,300
Since she was two,
she's been through
six major operations.

1415
01:19:43,343 --> 01:19:46,825
 We just can't subject her 
to any more.

1416
01:19:48,435 --> 01:19:50,611
Please understand.

1417
01:19:55,355 --> 01:19:56,617
I do.

1418
01:20:05,235 --> 01:20:07,454
- I'm so sorry.
- Me, too.

1419
01:20:13,896 --> 01:20:15,854
- I'm going to
lose my daughter.
- Sarah: No.

1420
01:20:15,898 --> 01:20:18,074
We won't
let it happen, Jane.

1421
01:20:18,117 --> 01:20:19,945
Oh, right, how are you
gonna stop it?

1422
01:20:19,989 --> 01:20:22,295
What are you gonna say
under oath about my marriage?

1423
01:20:22,339 --> 01:20:25,559
That Michael was a--
a loving, considerate,
wonderful husband.

1424
01:20:25,603 --> 01:20:27,866
That-- that he was devoted
to me and my child.

1425
01:20:27,910 --> 01:20:30,608
That I must've
told you a million times
how lucky I was to have him.

1426
01:20:30,651 --> 01:20:33,089
Carole will testify
Michael lied to her.

1427
01:20:33,132 --> 01:20:35,047
Oh, did he? Did he?
Or was he just repeating

1428
01:20:35,091 --> 01:20:36,832
the things
his crazy wife told him?

1429
01:20:36,875 --> 01:20:39,530
Sarah, he's got
all the bases covered.

1430
01:20:39,573 --> 01:20:42,228
I was the one
who lost her memory.

1431
01:20:42,272 --> 01:20:44,187
 I was the one 
who tried to kill him.

1432
01:20:44,230 --> 01:20:46,015
I was the one
who locked Paula
in the bathroom

1433
01:20:46,058 --> 01:20:47,886
and broke into
his parents' house.

1434
01:20:47,930 --> 01:20:50,497
I don't think they won't be
only too happy to testify.

1435
01:20:50,541 --> 01:20:52,064
Even my own doctors
will say

1436
01:20:52,108 --> 01:20:53,892
I was suffering from
hysterical amnesia.

1437
01:20:53,936 --> 01:20:55,894
He was
feeding you drugs.

1438
01:20:55,938 --> 01:20:57,853
No, no, no,
I stole them
out of his bag.

1439
01:20:57,896 --> 01:20:59,463
He only injected me
when I was violent.

1440
01:20:59,506 --> 01:21:01,900
And Paula saw everything.

1441
01:21:01,944 --> 01:21:04,120
[ sighs ]

1442
01:21:06,600 --> 01:21:08,167
You still
don't get Michael,
do you?

1443
01:21:09,821 --> 01:21:12,302
He'll do anything
to get what he wants.

1444
01:21:12,345 --> 01:21:14,695
And he could win this.

1445
01:21:18,482 --> 01:21:21,093
It's time
for Amy and me
to disappear.

1446
01:21:21,137 --> 01:21:23,922
 Do you wanna lose 
all chances of custody?

1447
01:21:23,966 --> 01:21:25,315
Michael will find you.

1448
01:21:25,358 --> 01:21:27,012
He won't find us.

1449
01:21:27,056 --> 01:21:29,058
So you're gonna
spend your life running,

1450
01:21:29,101 --> 01:21:31,321
looking over
your shoulder?

1451
01:21:31,364 --> 01:21:33,671
- What kind of life
is that for Amy?
- What kind of a life is it

1452
01:21:33,714 --> 01:21:35,629
if Michael gets custody?

1453
01:21:37,414 --> 01:21:39,982
I can't trust
the legal system.

1454
01:21:40,025 --> 01:21:41,592
Michael has
all the cards.

1455
01:21:44,203 --> 01:21:46,075
I'll go to that meeting

1456
01:21:46,118 --> 01:21:48,207
at his lawyer's
office tomorrow
to show good faith.

1457
01:21:48,251 --> 01:21:50,949
But if we can't
come to an agreement,
we're out of here.

1458
01:21:50,993 --> 01:21:54,083
 [ phone rings ]

1459
01:21:55,301 --> 01:21:57,564
- Yes?
- Jane?

1460
01:21:57,608 --> 01:21:59,131
This is Paula Marinelli.

1461
01:21:59,175 --> 01:22:00,654
How'd you get
this number?

1462
01:22:00,698 --> 01:22:02,265
Dr. Ravenson.

1463
01:22:03,657 --> 01:22:05,050
I need to talk to you.

1464
01:22:05,094 --> 01:22:06,704
No, we have nothing
to talk about.

1465
01:22:06,747 --> 01:22:08,227
No, wait, Jane.
Please, you don't--

1466
01:22:08,271 --> 01:22:09,968
 [ dial tone ]

1467
01:22:12,362 --> 01:22:13,929
Michael.

1468
01:22:15,278 --> 01:22:17,323
No, he's not
that obvious.

1469
01:22:18,846 --> 01:22:21,284
He sends Paula
to do his dirty work.

1470
01:22:25,723 --> 01:22:27,333
 [ phone ringing ]

1471
01:22:31,033 --> 01:22:32,338
 [ horn honks ]

1472
01:22:34,340 --> 01:22:36,429
Listen, since
my wife's attorney
has been delayed,

1473
01:22:36,473 --> 01:22:38,214
I'd like to talk to her
in private.

1474
01:22:41,130 --> 01:22:42,566
I don't think
that's unreasonable.

1475
01:22:44,698 --> 01:22:46,048
Mrs. Ravenson?

1476
01:22:48,398 --> 01:22:51,618
I certainly don't want
to appear unreasonable.

1477
01:22:55,274 --> 01:22:57,668
I'll be
right outside the door
in case you need me.

1478
01:22:57,711 --> 01:22:59,713
I'm only dangerous
when the moon is full.

1479
01:23:02,716 --> 01:23:04,544
It's just Jane's humor.

1480
01:23:09,810 --> 01:23:12,030
 [ phone rings ]

1481
01:23:12,074 --> 01:23:13,858
[ sighs ]

1482
01:23:13,901 --> 01:23:16,252
I thought we could
talk to each other
like two adults.

1483
01:23:16,295 --> 01:23:19,037
That's interesting
for a man who prefers
children.

1484
01:23:20,299 --> 01:23:21,822
You're not
making this easy.

1485
01:23:21,866 --> 01:23:24,738
Well, I forgot to take
my Haldol this morning.

1486
01:23:24,782 --> 01:23:27,654
Jane, I know
what you think
I've done, but--

1487
01:23:27,698 --> 01:23:30,962
Save the lies
for the courtroom, Michael.

1488
01:23:32,659 --> 01:23:34,226
I want you back.

1489
01:23:38,056 --> 01:23:39,101
I love you.

1490
01:23:41,103 --> 01:23:42,582
I know you don't
believe that.

1491
01:23:42,626 --> 01:23:45,194
You think I'm
some kind of a monster,

1492
01:23:45,237 --> 01:23:46,630
but I love you.

1493
01:23:46,673 --> 01:23:50,416
I want this nightmare
to be over.

1494
01:23:50,460 --> 01:23:53,332
I want you and Amy
to come back home

1495
01:23:53,376 --> 01:23:55,247
where you belong.

1496
01:23:55,291 --> 01:23:57,597
You want.

1497
01:23:57,641 --> 01:23:59,860
You want this,

1498
01:23:59,904 --> 01:24:01,645
you want that.

1499
01:24:11,089 --> 01:24:13,004
Here, open it.

1500
01:24:13,048 --> 01:24:14,397
